            <codeblock>

&lt;level leveltype="section"&gt;
    ...
    &lt;bodytext&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;
            &lt;text&gt;Tier 2 (Intra-Company Transfer) (ICT) allows businesses with linked entities
                overseas to transfer certain non-European Economic Area (EEA) national employees to
                work in their UK offices. Partners in business structures such as Limited Liability
                Partnerships are treated as employees for these purposes. There are now four
                separate ICT sub-categories which have different eligibility criteria. If the
                relevant criteria are met, there is no requirement for a sponsor to carry out a
                Resident Labour Market Test.&lt;/text&gt;
        &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/bodytext&gt;
    &lt;bodytext&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;
            &lt;text&gt;The route is not included in the limits on non-EEA immigration, and sponsors are
                able to request the number of 'unrestricted' Certificates of Sponsorship (CoS) they
                require under each ICT sub-category on an annual basis.&lt;/text&gt;
        &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/bodytext&gt;
    ...
&lt;/level&gt;

           </codeblock>
            <title>Target XML</title>
            <codeblock>

&lt;seclaw:level leveltype="section"&gt;
    ...
    &lt;seclaw:bodytext&gt;
